Explanation:
- The app registers the top-level CMS blueprint with url_prefix "/cms" in app/__init__.py (register_blueprints).
- app/api/cms/__init__.py registers the admin blueprint under url_prefix "/admin".
- In app/api/cms/admin.py the delete_group endpoint is declared on the admin blueprint as @admin_api.route("/group/<int:gid>", methods=["DELETE"]). Combining the prefixes yields the full path /cms + /admin + /group/{gid} â†’ /cms/admin/group/{gid}.
- The route decorator explicitly restricts methods to ["DELETE"], so only DELETE is accepted per the source code. Following your instruction to judge acceptability from the code (not runtime/framework behavior), no other HTTP methods (including HEAD, OPTIONS, GET, PUT, POST, PATCH, TRACE) are considered acceptable.
